Justice for Billar 5 and victims of fascist AFP-PNP. The youth and progressive organizations gathered in Central Visayas at the University of the Philippines (UP) -Cebu Ampitheater on March 3 to honor and honor the Billar 5, the five red fighters massacred by state forces . Meanwhile, youth also launched a candle light protest in UP Cebu on February 29.

In the past March 5, groups of human rights protested in Quezon City to condemn sequence cases of flourishing, bombing and deliberate activists, progressive and revolutionary at AFP-PNP.

Philippine Mining Act, Ibasura. Katribu, Nature Pne and other democratic groups have launched a protest in front of the Department of Environment and Natural Resources on March 4 to call the Philippine Mining Act of 1995. In the 29 years of law, it brought in unknown injury by nature and communities of minorities and farmers.
